Notes on scope of this licence

* The code, scripts, data fixtures, and visualisation components in this
  repository are released under the MIT License above. Commercial use,
  modification, and redistribution are permitted, subject to the attribution
  requirement.

* The written content under `content/` (page copy, DM drafts, interview
  Q&A, mock-interview script, demo walkthrough) and the slide deck under
  `slides/` were prepared for a specific job-application context. They
  are released under the same MIT License for clarity, but if you plan to
  reuse them as templates for your own application, please adapt
  substantively — the value is in the methodology, not in re-using
  identical phrasing.

* All numerical assumptions in the NAV stress model (sub-sector stress
  calibrations, facility sizings, covenant levels, hypothetical fund
  profiles in `data/`) are illustrative. Nothing in this repository
  constitutes financial advice, investment recommendations, credit
  analysis, or an authoritative view on any institution's product or
  pricing.

* "UniCredit", "Politecnico di Milano", and any other organisation names
  mentioned in the documentation are referenced for context only; their
  appearance does not imply endorsement, affiliation, or review by those
  organisations.
